[{"id":"d9a5e676-66cc-4166-adaf-509477252992","cell_type":"code","source":"import numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\nimport matplotlib.gridspec as gridspec\n\n# --- CONFIGURATION: MULTI-EPOCH SIMULATION ---\ndt = 0.001          # Moderate precision for longer timeframe\nepoch_duration = 20.0 # Each problem lasts 20 seconds\nnum_epochs = 5      # The agent faces 5 problems in a row\ntotal_steps = int(epoch_duration * num_epochs / dt)\ntime = np.linspace(0, epoch_duration * num_epochs, total_steps)\n\n# --- PHYSICAL CONSTANTS ---\ngamma = 5.0\nk_native = 10.0\nk_archive = 2000.0  # The Crystal Stiffness\nflash_cost_base = 300.0 # The initial cost of insight\n\nclass MemoryAgent:\n    def __init__(self, mode):\n        self.mode = mode # 'tedious', 'kinexis_basic', 'kinexis_memory'\n        self.work = np.zeros(total_steps)\n        self.precision = np.zeros(total_steps)\n        \n        # Memory State\n        self.cached_knowledge = 0.0 # \"Memory Step Up\" factor\n    \n    def run(self):\n        current_x = 5.0 # Start in chaos\n        cumulative_work = 0.0\n        \n        for i in range(total_steps):\n            # Detect Epoch Change (New Problem arrives)\n            if i % int(epoch_duration/dt) == 0 and i > 0:\n                # Reset Chaos for the new problem\n                current_x = 5.0 \n            \n            # 1. Determine Current Parameters\n            # Tedious always struggles\n            k_eff = k_native \n            \n            # Kinexis Logic\n            step_flash_cost = 0\n            if 'kinexis' in self.mode:\n                # If we are close enough to \"Precision\" state\n                if abs(current_x) < 1.5:\n                    # BASIC KINEXIS: Pays full cost every time it locks in\n                    if self.mode == 'kinexis_basic':\n                        k_eff = k_archive\n                        # We simulate \"Paying the Flash\" continuously to hold the lock \n                        # or a one-time fee per epoch. Let's say one-time per epoch.\n                        if i % int(epoch_duration/dt) == 100: # Trigger early in epoch\n                            step_flash_cost = flash_cost_base\n\n                    # MEMORY STEP UP: Cost decreases based on cache\n                    elif self.mode == 'kinexis_memory':\n                        k_eff = k_archive\n                        if i % int(epoch_duration/dt) == 100:\n                            # Cost is discounted by memory\n                            cost = flash_cost_base * (1.0 - self.cached_knowledge)\n                            step_flash_cost = max(cost, 10.0) # Min cost to reference\n                            \n                            # STEP UP: Successful application increases memory cache\n                            self.cached_knowledge = min(self.cached_knowledge + 0.25, 0.95)\n\n            # 2. Physics (Simplified Langevin for speed)\n            # F_restore\n            f_restore = -k_eff * current_x\n            \n            # Noise (Tedious has high noise, Archive has low)\n            noise_mag = 5.0 if k_eff == k_native else 0.1\n            f_noise = np.random.normal(0, noise_mag)\n            \n            # Dynamics\n            dx = (f_restore + f_noise) / gamma * dt\n            current_x += dx\n            \n            # 3. Work Calculation\n            # Power = F^2 / gamma\n            power = (f_restore**2) / gamma\n            work_instant = power * dt + step_flash_cost\n            cumulative_work += work_instant\n            \n            self.work[i] = cumulative_work\n            self.precision[i] = 1.0 / (abs(current_x) + 0.01) # Inverse error\n\n# --- EXECUTION ---\nprint(\"Simulating Memory Step Up across 5 Cognitive Epochs...\")\nagent_tedious = MemoryAgent('tedious')\nagent_basic = MemoryAgent('kinexis_basic')\nagent_memory = MemoryAgent('kinexis_memory')\n\nagent_tedious.run()\nagent_basic.run()\nagent_memory.run()\n\n# --- VISUALIZATION ---\nplt.style.use('dark_background')\nfig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))\ngs = gridspec.GridSpec(1, 2)\n\n# Plot 1: Cumulative Work (The Efficiency Staircase)\nax1 = plt.subplot(gs[0, 0])\nax1.plot(time, agent_tedious.work, color='#FF4444', label='Tedious (Brute Force)')\nax1.plot(time, agent_basic.work, color='#FFFF00', linestyle='--', label='Kinexis (No Memory)')\nax1.plot(time, agent_memory.work, color='#00FFAA', linewidth=2.5, label='Kinexis + Memory Step Up')\n\n# Mark Epochs\nfor e in range(1, num_epochs):\n    ax1.axvline(e * epoch_duration, color='white', alpha=0.1, linestyle=':')\n\nax1.set_title('Cumulative Metabolic Cost (5 Problems)', fontsize=14, color='white')\nax1.set_ylabel('Energy Expended', fontsize=12)\nax1.set_xlabel('Time (s) - New Problem every 20s', fontsize=12)\nax1.legend()\nax1.grid(True, alpha=0.1)\n\n# Plot 2: Cost Per Epoch (The Learning Curve)\nax2 = plt.subplot(gs[0, 1])\nepochs = range(1, num_epochs + 1)\n# Extract cost incurred during each epoch\ndef get_epoch_costs(agent):\n    costs = []\n    for e in range(num_epochs):\n        start = int(e * epoch_duration / dt)\n        end = int((e+1) * epoch_duration / dt) - 1\n        costs.append(agent.work[end] - agent.work[start])\n    return costs\n\ncosts_tedious = get_epoch_costs(agent_tedious)\ncosts_basic = get_epoch_costs(agent_basic)\ncosts_memory = get_epoch_costs(agent_memory)\n\nwidth = 0.25\nax2.bar(np.array(epochs)-width, costs_tedious, width, color='#FF4444', label='Tedious')\nax2.bar(np.array(epochs), costs_basic, width, color='#FFFF00', label='Kinexis (Standard)')\nax2.bar(np.array(epochs)+width, costs_memory, width, color='#00FFAA', label='Kinexis (Memory)')\n\nax2.set_title('Energy Cost Per Problem (The Ratchet Effect)', fontsize=14, color='white')\nax2.set_ylabel('Cost per Problem', fontsize=12)\nax2.set_xlabel('Problem Sequence #', fontsize=12)\nax2.legend()\n\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.show()\n\n# --- ANALYSIS REPORT ---\nprint(\"--- MEMORY STEP UP ANALYSIS ---\")\nprint(f\"Problem 1 Cost (Memory Agent): {costs_memory[0]:.2f}\")\nprint(f\"Problem 5 Cost (Memory Agent): {costs_memory[-1]:.2f}\")\nimprovement = (costs_memory[0] - costs_memory[-1]) / costs_memory[0] * 100\nprint(f\"Optimization Factor: {improvement:.2f}% reduction in effort over time.\")","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":"Simulating Memory Step Up across 5 Cognitive Epochs...\n"},{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1600x800 with 2 Axes>","image/png":""},"metadata":{}},{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":"--- MEMORY STEP UP ANALYSIS ---\nProblem 1 Cost (Memory Agent): 2916.89\nProblem 5 Cost (Memory Agent): 2917.37\nOptimization Factor: -0.02% reduction in effort over time.\n"}],"execution_count":1}]
